div.bibl: Dziennik Chicagoski, June 26, 1896. MORE DONATIONS FOR THE SAINT JOHN CANTIUS PARISH FAIR

body.p: The following additional donations have been received for the Saint John Cantius Parish fair:
John Malinowski, $1; T. Suchowski, 260 Sangamon Street, one wagon and two
goats, valued at eighteen dollars; E. Jalowy, 66 Wesson Street, $1;
M. Koveny, 71 Wesson Street, $1; J. Dziewior, 108 Wesson Street, $1;
J. Dziewior, 114 Wesson Street, $2; P. Budzban, 114 Wesson Street, $1;
F. Koloch, 118 Wesson Street, $1; S. Adamik, 124 Wesson Street, 50 cents;
M. Dziewior, 124 Larrabee Street, $5; I. Roda, 49 Rosby Street, $1;
M. Ogorek, 66 Wesson Street, 50 Cents; W. Migats, 16 Wesson Street, 50 cents;
P. Botow, 38 Fry Street, 50 cents; J. Brzezinski, 40 Fry Street, $1;
M. Siracki, 40 Fry Street, $1; M. Markowski, 40 Fry Street, $1;
P. Rekowski, 91 Fry Street, $1; Felix Bukowski, 91 Fry Street, $1;
J. Kwasniewski, 91 Fry Street, $1; J. Sikorski, 25 cents; F. Walecka,
25 cents; R. S. Kurnlerr, 109 Cornelia Street, one barrel of flour;

S. Ptaszynski, 98 Cornelia Street, one box of candy; F. Klemunt, 93 Cornelia Street, one barrel of flour; John Danielewicz, 14 Lessing Street, 50 cents; Joan Danielewicz, 14 Lessing Street, one toilet set; and Peter Rostenkowski, 75 Cleaver Street, one canary in its cage.
A God bless you to all the donors!
